The book complements Supporting Business Environment Reforms by the DCED (2008), which provides the standard methodological framework for implementing business environment reform projects, but lacks adequate guidance on gender considerations. The DCED is in the process of writing a gender annex to their 2008 guidance, which should be available in late 2016.  This is expected to include a wealth of new information about donors' experience with gender-sensitive programming that was not available in 2010.
